<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2AAFF72FC4FFED5" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2AAFF72FC4FFED5" blockId="7.[151,1437,224,466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935E8E03F2AAFF72FC4BFED5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147330" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F034FF72FDA1FF31" box="[521,624,224,250]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “male symbol”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F653FF72FB1FFF31" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1134,1230,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sobrinus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F653FF72FB1FFF31" box="[1134,1230,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">sobrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Pyr. or.” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F29CFE96FEC5FED5" box="[161,276,260,286]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F304FE96FD77FED5" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[313,678,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sobrinus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F304FE96FDDBFED5" box="[313,522,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus sobrinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F02CFE96FD77FED5" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[529,678,260,286]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935E8E03F127FE96FC5EFED5" box="[794,911,260,286]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2FAFEBAFB82FE19" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2FAFEBAFE6CFE65" blockId="7.[151,1437,224,466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
This name has been currently considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F171FEBAFB2FFE89" authority="(Duftschmid, 1812)" baseAuthorityName="Duftschmid" baseAuthorityYear="1812" box="[844,1278,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F171FEBAFBCBFE89" box="[844,1050,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus rubripes</emphasis>
(Duftschmid, 1812)
</taxonomicName>
, a species that shows red coloured femurs in other areas of West Europe. Traditional works as those of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F649FEDEFAC0FEAD" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[1140,1297,332,358]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F775FEDEFF33FE41" author="Jeannel, R." pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel (1942)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F35AFEE2FE39FE41" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[359,488,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sobrinus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F35AFEE2FE39FE41" box="[359,488,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">H. sobrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a mere variation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F0F8FEE2FC97FE41" baseAuthorityName="Duftschmid" baseAuthorityYear="1812" box="[709,838,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F0F8FEE2FC97FE41" box="[709,838,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">H. rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a criterion also followed in the Palaearctic Catalogue (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F2A2FE06FE61FE65" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[159,432,404,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="1810" refId="ref11718" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 c) Subtribe Harpalina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 515 - 562." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2FAFE2AFB82FE19" blockId="7.[151,1437,224,466]" box="[199,1107,440,466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F2FAFE2AFE46FE19" baseAuthorityName="Duftschmid" baseAuthorityYear="1812" box="[199,407,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F2FAFE2AFE46FE19" box="[199,407,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Asiatic European element found from 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935E8E03F1B8FE2AFC19FE19" box="[901,968,440,466]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">China</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935E8E03F1D1FE2AFB9EFE19" box="[1004,1103,440,466]" name="Portugal" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Portugal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
